main event: A moving star-like light was observed traveling from north to east-southeast in Jacksonville, Florida.
interesting points: The object was described as moving very fast and different from an airplane or aircraft.
The observer stated the object went too fast and was a lighter color than a typical airplane.
No sound, odor, or heat was reported coming from the object.
The object did not disturb the ground or leave any physical evidence.
The observer had not seen this or a similar phenomenon before.
